Online Learning Resources and Support

Spring 2021  From building wearable technology to creating music and theatrical presentations, faculty at the University of Illinois Chicago have been working to provide students with opportunities for great online learning experiences. As the academic year continues into the Spring semester you can continue to read about students and faculty engaging in cutting-edge learning and teaching experiences.  You can also access online resources for learning and student services and see what life is like on UIC’s vibrant campus. 
Read the latest Circle Back to Campus newsletter
Online Learning: Faculty and Student PerspectivesVirtual ‘Mindful Mondays’ offer support to UIC student-athletes   Student-athletes take part in a program called “Mindful Mondays” that provides them an hour every week to gather virtually to discuss issues that may be on their minds Learn moreOnline learning   helped English language instructor explore new ways of teaching  UIC Tutorium in Intensive English in the Office of Global Engagement, helps students learn English to achieve their academic, professional and personal goals Learn moreWearable technology course expands to meet demandAs the COVID -19 pandemic continues, the need to be constantly aware of one’s own medical and fitness data has meant a rise in the demand for fitness trackers and wearable technologyLearn more
Serving students while teaching about global pandemic through e-learningSandra Gibbons, a lecturer in biological sciences, took advantage of the additional time before spring break to prepare to teach remotely.Learn moreStudents in virtual course delve into archives to analyze role of women in politics in 20th century Chicago The UIC course, Women and Politics in 20th Century Chicago, is being presented during the spring semester by David Greenstein.Learn moreOnline learning boosts class participationUrban Planning and Policy Assistant Professor Ning Ai  found the online platform to be a success for her studentsLearn more
My online learning experience at UIC: Tyra PattersonUIC student Tyra describes her experience learning online Learn moreFirst-year writing course increases belonging and retention New research suggests a reading-and-writing exercise about social belonging is an effective strategy to help student performance at urban, broad-access universities  Learn moreUIC lecturer creates structure through online learning College of Liberal Arts and Sciences Lecturer Karen Leick made the most of the transition to online learningLearn more
UIC Digital Humanities Initiative supports shift to e-learningSince classes were moved online, the initiative assisted faculty and instructors with the transition to the virtual classroomLearn more Nutritionist designs online curriculum to empower students in their home kitchens By having students work in their own homes and kitchens,  manager of the UIC Nutrition Garden Renea Lyles felt the new online learning reality was most applicable to studentsLearn moreMy online learning experience at UIC: Danielle HullUIC student Danielle shares her tips for online learningLearn more
